    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available now is an exceptional 1994 Mazda RX-7, presented in true collector-grade condition. This FD3S remains a mechanical benchmark, powered by its original 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, which delivers linear boost across the entire RPM range. The chassis retains its factory-spec 50/50 weight distribution, supported by pristine aluminum double-wishbone suspension and four-piston front calipers. Power is transferred via a crisp five-speed manual transmission to a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal corner-exit traction. The intricate vacuum system and solenoid rack have been meticulously maintained, preserving the factory boost curve. With zero signs of heat-cycling fatigue or oil seepage, this vehicle represents a rare opportunity to own a rotary icon that performs exactly as it did when it left Hiroshima.",
